<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-22T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-22T06:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/243</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-22T12:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1918, noon.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.06 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2073. Referring to the Legation’s No. 2072, 22d. Our British and
                                French colleagues concur in the opinion that the importation into
                                Denmark of the commodities designed to relieve Danish unemployment
                                before the conclusion of the negotiations now in progress would
                                sensibly weaken our position and consequently jeopardize their
                                consummation.</p>
                            <closer>[<signed><persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                                    </persName></signed>]</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>